On 1/4/2010 9:53 AM, Eduardo Romero wrote:

> .- file /usr/share/spamassassin/72_active.cf

According to http://wiki.apache.org/spamassassin/RuleUpdates, this 
should probably be /var/lib/spamassassin or something similar, under /var.

> .- add score 0 to this rule at /usr/share/spamassassin/50_scores.cf

This should probably go in your local.cf so you don't wipe it out 
accidentally.

> The 'sa-update' options not always works for me.

Yes, on my system it turned out sa-update was working just fine, but 
some programs were looking at the wrong set of rules so it looked like 
sa-update wasn't working.
